--TEST--
Installing a package with features that have conflicting dependencies should fail with a clear message
--COMPOSER--
{
    "repositories": [
        {
            "type": "package",
            "package": [
                {
                    "name": "a/a",
                    "version": "1.0.0",
                    "features": {
                        "b": {
                            "description": "Feature B",
                            "require": {
                                "b/b": "1.0.0"
                            }
                        },
                        "b-next": {
                            "description": "Feature B Next",
                            "require": {
                                "b/b": "2.0.0"
                            }
                        }
                    }
                },
                { "name": "b/b", "version": "1.0.0" },
                { "name": "b/b", "version": "2.0.0" }
            ]
        }
    ],
    "require": {
        "a/a": "1.0.0"
    },
    "require-features": {
        "a/a": ["b", "b-next"]
    }
}
--RUN--
update
--EXPECT-EXIT-CODE--
2

--EXPECT-OUTPUT--
Loading composer repositories with package information
Updating dependencies
Your requirements could not be resolved to an installable set of packages.

  Problem 1
    - Root composer.json requires a/a 1.0.0 -> satisfiable by a/a[1.0.0].
    - a/a 1.0.0 requires b/b 1.0.0 (using feature "b") -> found b/b[1.0.0] but these were not loaded, likely because it conflicts with another require.

--EXPECT--
